sentences.english: And I think you have to do the same with Dylan.
sentences.chinese: 所以在听迪伦的时候你也得这么想。

sentences.english: Otherwise, as Dylan says, if you're not busy being born, you're busy dying.
sentences.chinese: 否则，就如迪伦所说，不忙于求生，就是在找死。

sentences.english: Bob Dylan released 2 very different-sounding albums this year.
sentences.chinese: 鲍勃迪伦今年发行了两张乐风截然不同的专辑。

sentences.english: Album No. 3, "In the Wind, " featured three songs by the 22-year-old Dylan.
sentences.chinese: 专辑第3号“在风中，”推荐的三首歌22岁的迪伦。

sentences.english: She is married to actor Dylan Baker.
sentences.chinese: 她嫁给了演员迪伦贝克。

sentences.english: There have been rumours that Dylan was involved with heroin.
sentences.chinese: 以前就有传言说迪伦曾经吸食过海洛因。

sentences.english: Dylan, Berlin, Bay of Pigs invasion.
sentences.chinese: 鲍勃迪伦，柏林，猪湾事件。

sentences.english: Do you have any favorite Dylan songs?
sentences.chinese: 你最喜欢的歌曲里有迪伦的吗？

sentences.english: The Dillon Residence takes the form of a courtyard house typology.
sentences.chinese: 迪伦住宅选取了四合院的布局。

sentences.english: Does your generation still know who Bob Dylan is?
sentences.chinese: 你们这一代还知道谁是鲍勃迪伦吗？

sentences.english: The Adirondacks is somewhat different than the national parks.
sentences.chinese: 阿迪伦达克和国家公园相比有点儿不同。

sentences.english: Shelton then asks Dylan what would make him happy.
sentences.chinese: 谢尔顿接下来问迪伦怎么才能让他快乐呢。

sentences.english: Every time I gave the bird something to say, Dylan started trying to say the same thing.
sentences.chinese: 每次我教这只鸟说话时，迪伦也尝试说同样的东西。

definition: Jean-Paul Sartre (1905-1980), French existential philosopher and novelist
